text = "For visual clarity, we animate the robot as it travels from cell to cell.

This works for a pre-defined grid, but this function wouldn't work if we change the size of the grid. The robot would either stop before the end, or go too far.

The robot needs to move to the right until it gets to the end.

For code that repeats, we use [i]loops[/i].

While loops make the computer repeat a block of code until you meet a specific condition or decide to break from the loop.

Instead of the above, we can use a while loop."
